President Obama met with Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India to discuss their efforts to address global climate change. They emphasized the urgent threat posed by climate change and their commitment to a successful agreement in Paris. Both leaders agreed that the agreement should drive serious action to curb carbon pollution while allowing countries like India to prioritize development, growth, and poverty eradication. They committed their teams to work closely together to achieve these objectives. President Obama also praised Prime Minister Modi's initiatives to increase renewable energy deployment, his leadership in forming a solar alliance, and their partnership in launching Mission Innovation, an initiative to accelerate the development and deployment of affordable clean energy technology worldwide. The leaders also discussed strengthening their countries' strategic partnership on various issues.